  <summary>12/20/2001--Introduced.
National Border Security Agency Act - Establishes the National Border Security Agency, which shall plan and coordinate Federal border security activities, and act as a focal point for immigration enforcement.Transfers to the Agency the United States Coast Guard, the United States Customs Service, and specified portions of the Immigration and Naturalization Service.</summary>
